The course covers the following topics:
* Capital Assets Pricing Model incorporating corporate and individual income tax (TAX CAPM)
* Relationships between individual income tax and company valuation models
* Valuation of an unleveraged company 
* Valuation of a company with passive debt management
* Valuation of a company with active debt management
* Company valuation in the context of share buybacksObjectives/eesmärkid:  The objective of the course is to provide students with in-depth knowledge on how to incorporate personal taxes into company valuation using the DCF method.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of the course, the student will acquire: - Theoretical in-depth knowledge on the impact of both corporate and individual level taxes on company valuation models. - Understanding of how to accurately incorporate active and passive capital structure management and share buybacks into valuation of a company.  - Ability to create a valuation models in MS Excel that takes into account individual level taxes.
